Section 17: Spring JMS Support
 Lecture 92: Using Spring to send JMS Messages

 1. Add Spring JMS Maven Dependencies
  1.1 Spring JMS
    <dependency>
  	    <groupId>org.springframework</groupId>
  	    <artifactId>spring-jms</artifactId>
    </dependency>

  1.2 Apache ActiveMQ
    <dependency>
  		<groupId>org.apache.activemq</groupId>
  		<artifactId>activemq-broker</artifactId>
  	</dependency>

 2. Configuring Spring Boot for JMS
  2.1 Add Spring Boot properties for JMS
   - application.properties
       spring.activemq.in-memory=true
       spring.activemq.pooled=false

 3. Using Spring to send JMS messages
  3.1 Add Spring JMS config
   - ej.springframework.config.JMSConfig.java
  3.2 Define JMS Interface
   - ej.springframework.services.SenTextMessageService.java
  3.3 Implements JMS Interface
   - ej.springframework.services.SendTextMessageServiceImpl.java

 4. Applying JMS in to the ej.springframework.services.reposervices.ProductServiceRepoImpl.java
  4.1 Add ProductToProductForm properties
  4.2 Inject setter base ProductToProductForm dependency
  4.3 Add SendTextMessageService properties
  4.4 Inject setter base SendTextMessageService dependency
  4.5 Add sendTextMessageService... into the List<?> listAll() method
  4.6 Add sendTextMessageService... into the getById(..) method

5. Start and Check the Console that ActiveMQ
